I've set up a tailscale vpn following https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tnsrnsy_Lus&t=1724s : all commands are in show notes and here:

Command List
curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh
sudo tailscale up --ssh
tailscale status

sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
   ListenAddress 100.x.x.x 
  PasswordAuthenticationssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 kc@100.x.x.x
 no
  PermitRootLogin no

sudo systemctl restart ssh

adduser kc
usermod -aG sudo kc
su - kc
sudo whoami
logout
ssh kc@tailscale-ip


the vpn is working - it is set up in linux (but not android, which appears separate) you can login to the VPN through it- eg:

(base) ubuntu@penguin:~/node/imageai$ ssh root@image1

you can get a web dashboard by signing into login.tailscale.com

It appears that when enabled the VPN creates its own internal IP addresses/MagicDNS. Since MagicDNS is enabled, access a device signed in to your network by using its machine name. IP addresses are also available.

